    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>upon above inspiration i stopped by olive branch on 80th +lake city today; now the previous owner/proprietor used to serve the most perfect falafel i had had in the area&#8211;perfectly seasoned, encrusted in something smokey and nutty (pistachio, yes), served alongside the freshest of fresh, not too much tahini-yogurt, all wrapped in pita still piping hot, or nearly so, from the oven. i used to watch with amazement as neighborhood folks would stop in and have their pitas and flatbreads baked to order; nothing so cool as a tray of hot bread resembling mini-volleyballs before it does cool and flatten like griddlecakes. too bad she left. the place is still there and is still good&#8211;just not nearly what it once was. plus, it was closed today.</p>
    </div>

