    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://travelswithdarly.blogspot.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">darly gross</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/09/fallafel-and-gin-by-way-of-an-anniversary/#comment-650"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-03-17T15:51:00-04:00">Monday, March 17, 2008 at 3:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>respectfully, there is a better way to the perfect G/T. The ingredients are largely the same, but we add an important one, time. </></>Pour your gin of choice into a tall glass. Add the juice of half a lime, and the lime rind. Muddle, to release the rind&#8217;s oils, for :30 seconds. Then wait for a minimum of two minutes for everything to magically soften. (Ever eaten ceviche?)</></>Add a dash of bitters. Add fresh ice cubes, then slowly pour very fresh tonic from a fresh, small bottle (or fresh can; Whole Foods makes decent tonic) gently down the side of the glass. Add a fresh spritz of lime, and enjoy blissful repose, witty banter, and the light from the slanting sun. </></>-DRC</p>
    </div>

